review: Where's the worst restaraunt in Guildford? This is! Well, why is this restaraunt the worst? The following points will enlighten you: 1. The decor was bleak with very dim lighting. 2. Tables were sticky, even after telling the waiter, who was in a bad mood, nothing changed. 3. The food was obviously microwaved and yesterday's. It wasn't fresh by any stretch of the imagination. 4. It was really warm inside the restaraunt, making our experience that more terrible.

Went in Sunday night with barely 20% occupied in the Restaurant.. 2 of us went in took them 10mins to get us seated. Another 10mins to take order... 45 mins for the food to be served...  with the rudeness of staff~ Overall FOOD WAS AMAZING.. but service is HORRIBLE..

Lovely themed restaurant, tad overpriced, came here with my friends for a birthday meal only my parter and I ordered food as it was a bit expensive for us but we ordered drinks which were considerably reasonable and had a good time! Fun for parties just make sure to book a reservation!!
